</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Posterior nosebleed</strong> - Less common, occurring deep within the nose and often requiring medical attention.














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-41_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>In the UK, first aid for children in educational and care settings is governed by several pieces of legislation and guidelines:


<br>
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - Requires employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work.















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS)</strong> - Stipulates that all early years providers must have a paediatric first-aider available on the premises at all times children are present.















</li></ul><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-48_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Training providers, like The Mandatory Training Group, offer courses that ensure compliance with these regulations, enhancing safety and preparedness in child-centred environments.



