</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Positioning </strong>- Have the child sit up straight, and tilt their head slightly forward. Lying down or tilting the head back can cause blood to run down the throat.


















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Pinching the nose</strong> - Gently pinch the soft part of the nose (not the bone) between your thumb and finger. Hold it for ten minutes, and check if the bleeding has stopped.


















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Applying ice</strong> - Place a cold pack or wrapped ice on the bridge of the nose to help constrict the tiny blood vessels.



















</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>What to avoid
